{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Lower decibel limits for vehicle exhausts and monitor with noise cameras",
        "additional_details": "It is estimated that over 15% of the UK population is neurodivergent (including, but not limited to: Autistic, ADHD, and SPD). For those with diverse neurotypes, modified exhausts can be a sensory assault. Sudden, explosive noise can cause physical pain and trauma, especially for children. We have a right to access public spaces, yet avoidable noise can make our streets \"no-go zones.\" We call on the Government to mandate national acoustic camera enforcement to help protect all neurominorities.",
        "background": "Fund the nationwide roll-out of acoustic noise cameras and set stricter, lower enforceable decibel limits for vehicle exhausts.",
